  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter accompanies a box of contributions for the Boston Anti-Slavery Bazaar. Isabella Scott is the largest contributor to the fair. Margaret Armour is mentioned as one &quot;whose exertions have been valuable to us in making up our small stock this year.&quot; At a meeting called tomorrow to discuss the Fugitive Slave Law, Robert Edmond is expected to attend.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The second leaf of this manuscript consists of a &quot;list of articles sent to the Boston Anti-Slavery Bazaar 1850, from Edinburgh,&quot; including prices for the items.</subfield>
